        "## KEYWORD EXTRACTOR  \n  \n> Give instructions which types of keywords should be extracted in phase 1.\n>  \n>  \n>\n\n## LOAD FROM DIR  \n  \n> Enter path to image directory in \"directory\", in image load cap - entar how many images should load and lay ground for the prompt (between 1-100 images are okay).  \n  \n### RANDOM NUMBER  \n  \n> Enter the range of images in the load directory. For example, if you want to load 20 random images from a folder that contains 250 images: set minimum to 0 and maximum to 250.  \n  \n### CR Image Grid Panel  \n  \n> These are the settings how many columns etc you want the preview of your loaded images to be.  \n  \n### LOADED IMAGES  \n  \n> Here you can see which images have been loaded.  \n  \n### DELAY NODES  \n  \n> These are to slow down the calls between the Gemini nodes. If you are using free API you have a limited amount of calls per minute.  \n  \n### STUFF (GROUP)  \n  \n> These are your usual Flux nodes  \n  \n### GEMINI NODES  \n  \n> For instructions how to install and use these, visit [Github page](https://github.com/Creepybits/ComfyUI-Creepy_nodes)  \n  \n### CREEPY NODES  \n  \n> These are available both in ComfyUI Manager and on [Github](https://github.com/Creepybits/ComfyUI-Creepy_nodes)  \n  \n### USAGE  \n  \n> Use the workflow with Flux models or [Shuttle 3.1 Aesthetic](https://civitai.com/models/996504/shuttle-31-aesthetic) together with regular Flux VAE and CLIPS  \n  \n"
